Made in Europe offers to 105 newly vocational/high school graduated young people from Emilia Romagna Region, the opportunity to live a 3 months internship abroad (2 weeks for people with special needs and their accompanying people) in companies of other European countries, in order to gain professional, linguistic and cultural competences to be used on the labour market. 
The project is promoted by the Social Coop. Kara Bobowski in partnership with Irecoop and Concooperative Emilia Romagna, 5 technical and professional institutes (ITIS Baldini from Ravenna, ITI Garibaldi/Da Vinci from Cesena, ITS Calvi from Modena, IPSIA Cattaneo-Deledda from Modena, IIS Artusi from Forlimpopoli) and ITS per la Mobilità Sostenibile e la Logistica from Piacenza.
Made in Europe meets the need to support young graduates in facing the labour market and the need to create skilled labourforce in important fields of the regional economy: handicraft, agribusiness and agro-industry, mechanics, electronics, chemistry, logistic, hospitality and catering, tourism, social field, ICT.
They are people out of the European mobility projects of their school (mainly for students) and from those of the university that probably they will not attend.
The local and transnational partnership’s composition is strategic to the achievement of the project’s goals, networking among politics’authorities, representative institutions of the cooperative system, Chambers of Commerce, training centres, non-profit organizations, bodies specialized on international mobility. At national level, 8 consortium partners are involved plus 3 Italian realities supporting the project (Regione Emilia Romagna, Fondazione Cassa dei Risparmi Forlì, ANMIC Parma); at international level 12 foreign partners from 10 European countries are taking part to the project (France, Germany, UK, Spain, Malta, Hungary, Portugal, Finland, Lithuania, Poland).
The project’s aims are in line with the priorities and goals of Europe 2020 and Education and Training 2020 Strategies. The project wants to:
- offer a training opportunity to the participants, in order to improve their curricula and turn them more qualified and competitive on the labour market;
- promote creativity, competitiveness, employment and entrepreneurship;
- facilitate the passage to the labour market, thanks to an experience becoming strategic in a period of economic crisis and high youth unemployment;
- promote the opportunity of gaining competences within fields, which are strategic for the Emilia Romagna productive and economical system (cooperative, but not only); 
- promote social inclusion and active citizenship also for young people with special needs;
- thanks to the project partnership, strengthen the cooperation among bodies at regional and European level representing education and vocational training systems, non-formal education and  labour market, increasing their internationalisation level and the quality of their services;
- develop the consortium staff know-how in terms of project and quality management and networking, as also develop the European dimension of the involved partners;  
- thanks to the dissemination and valorisation activity, create an improving domino effect that bring to new collaborations on other mobility activities or other projects.
For each year of the project, the planned activities are:
- information and promotion (publication of a call, information meetings in the schools, etc.);
- candidates’ s selection;
- predeparture preparation (a 2 days training session): one day on the labour market and the cooperative enterprises system, one day on the forthcoming experience abroad with non-formal education activities, presentation of contents, administrative and logistic aspects, monitoring activities;  62 participant will use the dedicated  Online Platform for linguistic preparation; 
- mobility abroad (April-July 2016 and April-July 2017): cultural activities and 3 months internship (30-40 weekly hours) in a sector in line with their studies. 28 participants will take a short language course of the destination country mother language;
- at the end of the internship, back in Italy, a final activity including an evaluation phase with the participants, the coordinating body and all the consortium partners, and a public phase, including Europass official delivery, open to all the involved stakeholders. 
The whole project will be distinguished by a constant tutoring, mentoring, evaluation, validation and valorisation process.
The activities planning, the implementing and monitoring strategies, the local and transnational partnership composition, the dissemination and valorisation plan, will guarantee the project quality and the sustainability of its results. In particular the projects aims at producing such an impact to increase the mobilities number in the region, replicate the project, create a positive domino effect leading to new partnerships for new mobility projects or of other kind.

With the present application, Aula de Comércio intends to go on working what has been a priority in its Educational Project, namely, to make lifelong learning and mobility a reality to our students, promoting justness, social cohesion and active citizenship, motivating creativity and innovation.  
Once it is our mission to drive our students and trainers to participate in an Educational Project that enables them to successfully manage a personal and professional path throughout life, embracing the challenges of globalization, one can understand the common goal between Aula de Comércio and Erasmus + specific and operational aims:
• To support participants in work placements in other countries of EU and, thus, develop the acquisition and the use of knowledge, skills and qualifications to facilitate personal development, employability and the growth of an entrepreneurial spirit;
• To help improve the quality and innovation of our services, pedagogies and practices  in the field of education and training through permanent partnerships and cooperation with different companies and organizations throughout Europe, which enlighten us regarding the features and emergent needs of their different national realities;
• To increase attractiveness within vocational training, by making these mobility projects an attribute of each year of any course at Aula de Comércio;
• To contribute to a greater quality, transparency and recognition of qualifications and competences, by using, among others, the available Europass Documents.
Thus, at AC, the candidates for the curricular and professional work placements in the scope of Erasmus + Programme are students attending or that have graduated from a EU level 4 Course either on Commerce, Sales, Window Dressing, Computing/IT, Events Management, Hospitality, Restaurant and Bar Tending, Distribution, Logistics and Communication and Digital Service.
With this Application we would like to provide students of the different courses at AC the opportunity for a VET traineeship either in France (Paris), Spain (Barcelona) or in the United Kingdom (Cardiff and London), namely:
• 24 curricular vocational training placement mobilities of 6 weeks (students from 2nd year classes): 28th May till 6th July 2018;
• 16 vocational training placement mobilities of 6  months (recent graduates): January till June 2018;
• 50 curricular vocational training placement mobilities of 14 days hosted at a VET school with similar courses to Aula de Comércio: 27th may till 9th June 2018;
• 10 staff job shadowing mobilities in London, Barcelona, Paris and Raisio, Finland,  where trainers and staff will develop a work plan together with ECL partners and VET schools, regarding their professional needs/interests: January , if Course Coordinators , since their students are at work placements; or June, if other staff, since the majority of the students are doing their work placements.
The trainers that accompany the students are essential, once most of our 1st year students are under eighteen, therefore, we must make sure the work placement and work plan are suitable in what the objectives of the mobility are concerned and to accompany them throughtout their moblity.
This mobility project will answer to the training needs through the accomplishment of either curricular or professional work placements in companies of the Trade and Services sector where the participants will develop the activities defined in the Work Placement Guide Document of each course they attend. The translation (in the language of the host country) of this document is previously given to the intermediary partners and the host partners, for them to guarantee that the tasks in the Work Placement Activities Plan can be developed, guaranteeing motivated students and employers/companies and successful work placements.
The foreseen accompanying trainers are essential to guarantee that the planned objectives are executed, as well as in a perspective of a growing quality improvement, once they will share their recent apprenticeships with the school community, as the staff who will do job shadowing will.
As results, we intend that the participants in this mobility project, by developing personal, sociocultural, linguistic and professional competences in a different social, cultural and economic context, will show themselves to be competent in carrying out qualified jobs at any country of EU, and, therefore to best contribute to their personal and professional fulfilment as well as for a more cohesive Europe.

there are results of international research, (a.o. OECD and University of Auckland, New-Zealand) about sustainable integrated policy and leadership. These results form the basis of an international movement in education that works on the development and the realisation of a sustainable integrated qualitative policy in schools. This qualitative policy in schools has a positive impact on the learning of each learner: student, teacher, leader. The focus on the positive impact on the learning of each learner creates a flow in schools: school are encouraged to search systematically on how they can optimize their teaching in a sustainable way.

This international movement is in line with the expectations of inspection in Flanders. Inspection has created a frame of reference on quality in education. Starting from this frame of reference, the consortium has detected 5 attributes of quality. The consortium wants to learn about these 5 attributes and want to realise a sustainable policy on it. 
The consortium will work in the following attributes:
- to study and to develop systematically the quality of education;
- to develop and to realise a policy on effective professional development/ learning;
- to collaborate in a collegial and collaborative way to realise an integrated policy within schools;
- to optimise the learning process and the live and learning environment;
- to stimulate the learning and the development of all learners.

'Teams' from members of the consortium will attend international mobilities. They will share what they learned within their organisation. They will apply what they learn, share with colleagues and in networks. Advisors of the organisation of the coordinator will support the networks in Flanders. Members of the consortium will take what they learned on board in their strategic plan and share this with other members of the consortium and other schools.

Finally the members of the consortium will realise a sustainable qualitative educational policy. They will be able to proof to inspection that they realise qualitative education in their school.

The Consortium, through this project, wants to support young people just going out from school to enter the labour market and to develop skilled labour force for important fields of the regional economy: agriculture, agri-food and agro-industrial, hotel services, catering and tourism, educational and social-health field.
For this aim, MADE IN EUROPE+ offers to 94 graduates from Emilia-Romagna the opportunity to make a work experience in another EU country for 3 months (76 mobilities) and for 2 weeks for participants with special needs (18 mobilities).
The project’s aims are in line with priorities and goals of Erasmus+ and of the ET Strategy 2020. In particular, the project wants to:
-answer to the participants’ needs in terms of development of professional, linguistic and transversal knowledges and skills;
-offer a training opportunity to the participants, in order to turn them more competitive on the labour market and to help them to become autonomous young adults, enriched on a cultural and human level;
-promote creativity, employment and entrepreneurship with particular reference to some strategic fields of the regional economy and answer to some special requests from the labour market;
-offer a mobility opportunity for young people with special needs, little step to promote their inclusion and autonomy;
-strengthen the cooperation among organisations representing education, vocational training and  labour market, increasing their internationalisation level, the quality of their services, their staff’s know-how in terms of project and quality management and networking;
-create a so strong domino effect on participants, local and European partners and on the regional area to make the project sustainable and repeatable over the time.
In order to implement the project, the planned activities are:
-Advanced Preliminary Visit to 3 host partners;
- information and promotion, candidates’ selection;
-pre-departure training with activities about career guidance and interculturality as well as presentation about project’s contents and management. 65 participants will use the OLS for their linguistic preparation;
- mobility abroad (April-July and September-December 2019): 3 months internship in line with participants’ studies. 11 participants (in Slovenia and Lithuania) will take a short course in the language of the destination country. 2 weeks will be the length of the mobility for the participants with special needs and the presence of accompanying people is planned.
- at the end, once back to Italy, there will be a final meeting with the participants with evaluation and valorisation activities as well as activities about work and training guidance, ceremony of Europass and certificates delivering with the involvement of the Consortium, institutional partners and stakeholders.
The whole project will be distinguished by a constant tutoring, mentoring, evaluation, validation and valorisation process.
MADE IN EUROPE+ wants to start a virtuous circle, with a clear work-based learning approach,
starting from the training activities about the co-operative system done by Irecoop in schools, go through a professional experience abroad and end with the insertion into the labour market, supported by career training and guidance activities (always in the framework of the project and with a focus on the cooperative system).
The partnership composition, at local and transnational level, by networking different kind of actors (schools, vocational centres, companies, non-profit organizations, institutional bodies), is strategic for achieving the project objectives.
In particular, Kara Bobowski coordinates a Consortium composed by:
- the training institution Irecoop Emilia Romagna and its representative body Confcooperative
- 9 technical and vocational schools (Garibaldi/Da Vinci in Cesena, Calvi in Finale Emilia, Cattaneo-Deledda in Modena, Artusi in Forlimpopoli, Vergani-Navarra in Ferrara, Artusi in Riolo Terme, Ruffilli in Forlì, Paolini-Cassiano in Imola, Raineri-Marcora in Piacenza) and ANMIC Parma, as sending organisations.
There is also a support partnership that will guarantee visibility, sustainability and a close connection with the regional working world (Emilia Romagna Region, Consortium Winner Mestieri and 3 banks linked to the co-operative system).
The European partnership involves 11 organizations from the same number of countries: France, Austria, UK, Spain, Malta, Hungary, Portugal, Slovenia, Lithuania, Poland, Greece.
The activities planning, the implementation and monitoring strategies, the local and transnational partnership composition, the dissemination and valorisation plan will guarantee the quality of the project and the sustainability of its results. In particular the projects aims at producing such an impact to increase the mobilities number in the region, replicate the project in future, create a positive domino effect leading to new partnerships for new mobility projects or of other kind.

